    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P0133"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P0133",
      "text": "DTC P0133: LAF sensor response delay"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "17_3.0_jpn_11033515_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The LAF sensor detects the oxygen concentration in the exhaust gas and outputs a continuous signal; the PGM-FI ECU calculates the air-fuel ratio from the LAF sensor output signal value and performs fuel feedback control to further improve the exhaust gas condition. The PGM-FI ECU makes a positive or negative judgment of the sensor response characteristics by comparing the LAF sensor output value with the specified value. If the total LAF sensor output value is less than the specified value within the specified time, the PGM-FI ECU judges that the response performance of the LAF sensor has deteriorated and stores the DTC."
    },
