          "text": "LAF sensor degradation failure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reproducibility Testing Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "17_3.0_jpn_11033516_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Start the engine, run the radiator fan twice, and then warm up the engine for at least 2 minutes at 3,000 rpm with no load."
        },
        {
          "text": "Vehicle speed [vehicle speed] 40 km/h or less at a constant speed for at least 5 minutes."
        },
        {
          "text": "Immediately vehicle speed [vehicle speed] 41 km/h or more and engine rpm [engine rpm] 1,400-3,200*. 1 (3,700)* 2 Run at a constant speed of rpm for at least 8 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When conducting test drives, the driver must comply with all laws and regulations, observe good manners, and drive in accordance with the surrounding conditions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to have a fault, a temporary DTC is stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory. If the same failure is detected at the next D/C (two consecutive detections), the PGM-FI warning light comes on and the DTC and freeze data are stored."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is diagnosed and determined to be normal after running consecutive 3D/C runs, the PGM-FI warning light will turn off. In addition, the PGM-FI warning light, temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are cleared by using the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or by removing the 12V battery terminal."
    }
  ],
